<p>
    Cancer is a diverse group of proliferative diseases originating from abnormal cells that have the ability to grow without the limitations associated with normal tissue development. Uncontrolled cancer cell growth has one or more of the following characteristics: 1) independence from external growth promoting or arresting signals; 2) evasion of pro-apoptotic stimuli; 3) immortality; and 4) exploitation of the surrounding host tissue leading to vascularization and local/remote invasion.
