    <b>Medical Need:</b> In 2008, 2.8 million cancer deaths occurred in economically developed countries and 4.8 million in economically developing countries. More than 500,000 people were expected to die of cancer in the US. Cancer deaths in Africa totaled 512,400, with 681,000 new cases. For the majority of nonresectable cancers, treatment is largely ineffective.
